In [[number theory]], the '''diamond operators''' 〈''d''〉 are operators acting on the space of [[modular form]]s for the [[group (mathematics)|group]] Γ<sub>1</sub>(''N''), given by the action of a matrix ({{su|p=a b|b=c d}}) in  Γ<sub>0</sub>(''N''). The diamond operators form an [[abelian group]] and commute with the [[Hecke operator]]s.

== Unicode ==
In [[Unicode]], the diamond operator is represented by the character {{unichar|22C4|DIAMOND OPERATOR}}.
